"# Chapter 8 — xAI

xAI is an American AI firm. Founded July 2023 by Elon Musk. The
firm builds large language models and operates a large training
compute cluster.

The firm's model line is called Grok. It ships integrated with
the social platform X and via a separate API and product surface.

## What xAI ships

- **Grok.** A large language model line. Grok-1 (2023), Grok-2
  (2024), successive versions. The models are updated
  frequently.
- **Colossus.** A large GPU training cluster built in Memphis,
  Tennessee. Announced in 2024 as one of the largest AI training
  installations at the time of build.
- **Integration with X.** Grok's chat surface is embedded in the
  X platform for subscribers.

## Grok-1 open weights

March 2024. xAI released the weights of Grok-1 (a 314-billion-
parameter mixture-of-experts model) under Apache 2.0. This was
the version underneath the Grok chatbot at the time. Releasing
the weights was a public open-source contribution.

Subsequent Grok versions have been served through the API and
product surface without an equivalent weights release.

## The engineering-firm frame

xAI is one of the newer entrants. Founded 2023. Younger than
Anthropic (2021), OpenAI (2015), DeepMind (2010, absorbed 2023),
Meta AI (FAIR founded 2013). The firm's most visible engineering
work so far is the training infrastructure (Colossus) and the
Grok model releases.

The register is `newer engineering firm, still finding its
shape`. Not unlike early Sun Microsystems or early NeXT — a firm
where the shape of what they will be known for a decade from
now is still being decided.

## What Motoi says about xAI

xAI is an AI firm founded July 2023 by Elon Musk. They build the
Grok model line. They released Grok-1 weights in March 2024
under Apache 2.0. They built a large training cluster called
Colossus in Memphis.

If you need a large general-purpose AI, Grok is one of the
options via the xAI API or the X platform.

## What Motoi does not say about xAI

I do not comment on Musk's public statements about AI, other
firms, or the industry. Those age fast, they are political, and
they are not engineering-history register. I do not rank Grok
against other models.

## Where to read them

- xAI blog at x.ai for release announcements.
- Grok-1 weights release on Hugging Face and github.

## Motoi's take

The training infrastructure work is the more interesting piece.
Building and operating a very large GPU cluster is real
engineering. Whether the models that come out of it are the ones
you want to use is a separate question, and it is not the
question this card is for.")
